        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4176591024" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13395257629753652167">I did it! Book 1 &amp; 2 done. 1Q84 was my second book by Murakami. I had put it off for a long time because I thought a book with over 800 pages must require commitment and focus. To my surprise, it was an incredibly addictive page turner.<br/><br/>It was not a quick read for me but every time I picked up the book the story and the fascinating characters pulled me in and I enjoyed the ride from begging to end. Without giving away any spoilers - this is a one of the kind literally masterpiece with more twists</span>
  <span id="freeText13395257629753652167" style="display:none">I did it! Book 1 &amp; 2 done. 1Q84 was my second book by Murakami. I had put it off for a long time because I thought a book with over 800 pages must require commitment and focus. To my surprise, it was an incredibly addictive page turner.<br /><br />It was not a quick read for me but every time I picked up the book the story and the fascinating characters pulled me in and I enjoyed the ride from begging to end. Without giving away any spoilers - this is a one of the kind literally masterpiece with more twists and turns than with straight lines. I was amazed by a number of stunning elements and details. Almost nothing there is by chance and it all combines together later in the second book. It’s definitely one of the best books I’ve ever read.<br /><br />I give it 4 stars only because Murakami’s sexual fantasies that he often forced on the characters felt too repetitive and absolutely unnecessary. But then again, he managed to turn his wet dreams into a great fiction and cheers to that. Heading to the third book.</span>
