<span id="freeTextContainer7656656360468802628">This is a really enjoyable book. It&apos;s dreamy, easy to read yet substantial in scope, mysterious, different and intriguing. The characters and their roles will mystify and interest you. They circle around each other yet don&apos;t touch, alike yet different, the same yet opposites. Murakami spins their story flawlessly. <br/>At the end, it&apos;s still mysterious but also satisfying. <br/>This won&apos;t be the last of Murakami&apos;s books that I read. </span>
