  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3950262410" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3950262410" />
    <a title="Ailin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/130656899-ailin"><img alt="Ailin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1619579099p2/130656899.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3950262410?book_show_action=true">Apr 27, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ailin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ailin" href="/user/show/130656899-ailin">Ailin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780099549062" href="/book/show/15822556-1q84">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3950262410" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer33182734496620009">Hard to say how I feel about the 1Q84 series so far, two books in. At times it is slow, sometimes pleasantly so, other times to a fault. A lot of the text I&apos;m simply just not able to discern if I like or dislike. While some themes are unpleasant, that doesn&apos;t necessarily make them bad, but they at times seem unnecessary - especially as most of the reasons behind the happenings of this world remain a mystery for the majority of the books, which in itself isn&apos;t bad, quite the opposite, but it does</span>
  <span id="freeText33182734496620009" style="display:none">Hard to say how I feel about the 1Q84 series so far, two books in. At times it is slow, sometimes pleasantly so, other times to a fault. A lot of the text I'm simply just not able to discern if I like or dislike. While some themes are unpleasant, that doesn't necessarily make them bad, but they at times seem unnecessary - especially as most of the reasons behind the happenings of this world remain a mystery for the majority of the books, which in itself isn't bad, quite the opposite, but it doesn't always work in its favour. <br />I think around getting to Book 2, things actually start happening, and the "action" sets in, really bringing in some of the better aspects of the book and writing - the suspense, the tension, moments that actually has my heart beating faster and harder in anticipation.<br />While the characters are believable and interestingly unique and diverse at most times, sometimes the focus is left too long on some woman's breasts, too often, so that it feels almost out of character and is enough to pull you out of the story and just question the author a bit. <br />The book seems vague in it's language at times, so my review can't help but be as well. My view of the series is just a bit blurry for now. <br /><br />Still waiting to get my hands on the final part of the story in book 3. Perhaps I'll better know how I feel about this series then.</span>
  <a data-text-id="33182734496620009" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

